metadata.name: Aspergo #97
metadata.description:
A practice on texturing abstract paintings. Up to three techniques are applied by the painter to compose each image.

It may take a bit to start/finish depending on the features and cpu power, in any case i recommend to sit back and enjoy the painting process.

metadata.name: Sticky #8
metadata.description:
Experimenting with GL_LINES, instanced geometries and 3d flows.

Instructions:

- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'p' in 'Open live' to download the current view it in a custom resolution. This usually results in better quality for prints.

Happy New fxYear :)

Berlin, January 2022

metadata.name: de|growth:generations #36
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: Scattered Architectures #112
metadata.description:
“Scattered Architectures” is a generative experiment about the illusion of space created by flat surfaces that share edges.

This project drives inspiration from some beautiful drawings by Diane Scott: https://www.instagram.com/dianescottstudio/

Made by Leonardo Solaas

metadata.name: Annum #3455
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Chroma-Cube #17
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

#fxhashturnsone

'Chroma cube' consists of various colored geometric designs, arranged in a cube.

A donation from the primary sales will be made to the British Heart Foundation (BHF)

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 2000x2000px PNG.

metadata.name: Cheerful Obscure #51
metadata.description:
"Cheerful Obscure" is the 26th project I have minted on fxhash. For this project, I experimented with filling all the shapes with gradients. This is a gradient, that is a gradient, gradients everywhere!

Built on top of FX(STDIO)

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size (11x14" @ 150 dpi)
